    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix CRC computation error in iqplayer_loadfile due to incorrect pointer arithmetic\n\n### Summary\nThe iqplayer library in the OAI radio framework experiences CRC validation failures and data corruption when reading IQ samples from recorded files. This issue manifests as incorrect data being processed during replay mode, leading to false positive CRC errors in downstream processing functions.\n\nThe root cause was incorrect pointer arithmetic in multiple locations where data was being read from or written to wrong memory addresses. Specifically, when accessing data following an `iqrec_t` header structure, the code used `ptr+1` instead of `(char*)ptr + sizeof(iqrec_t)`, causing it to skip to the next `iqrec_t` structure rather than the immediate data area.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce this issue:\n1. Configure OAI with IQ replay mode using a recorded IQ file\n2. Run the gNB or UE with `--replay-file` option pointing to a valid IQ recording\n3. Observe CRC validation failures or incorrect data processing in the baseband processing chain\n4. The issue is more pronounced when using the non-mmap mode for file reading\n\n### Changes\n- `radio/iqplayer/iqplayer_lib.c`: \n  - Fixed redundant assignment of `s->ms_sample` in mmap mode\n  - Corrected memset size to cover entire allocated buffer including data area\n  - Fixed lseek return value check to properly validate file positioning\n  - Corrected pointer arithmetic when reading IQ data from file in non-mmap mode\n  - Fixed pointer arithmetic when copying data to output buffers\n"
}